<br>
As a manaburn wizard I can safely say Manaburn at the least should be disallowed for looting rights on a PvP kill.   manaburn trivializes PvP so the wizard gets no respect for victories.  In group pvP, however, I see how manaburn often plays an important roll in strategy, so I am reluctant to have them compeltely remove it from pvP as it gives us a JOB or an identity in group PvP.<br>
<br>
Let's face it, a cleric healing ANYONE versus our nukes makes wizards a joke in pvP, so in big group encoutners our nukes are somewhat frivilous to the often 4 to 7k hps of players who are getting Celstial Elixered and CHd.  manaburn allows us to take out a cleric right away from the battle which at least makes us useful.<br>
<br>
I don't think we are weak in pvP, but your story was lopsided ;p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usollaiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sollaiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/29/02 9:28:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Nerfing manaburn is acceptable, if the PvP resists are nerfed as well.. <br>
